title: kfv-mode-video.ogv
description:
This is a demonstration video of KFV Mode, a program that can help the Kernel Freedom Verification project of the gNewSense GNU/Linux distribution.  This project aims to  document the free and non-free parts of the Linux kernel in order to distribute only the free software subset of the Linux kernel and in this way respect users&#039; freedoms.

KFV Mode runs under the Emacs text editor, and the video tries not to assume too much knowledge of Emacs.  It runs about 9 minutes, a little over 50 MB, and is at a 1024x768 resolution for readability.
